          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Expanded Access to Opioid Abuse Treatment Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Controlled Substances Act to allow a pharmacist who meets specified criteria to be a qualifying practitioner who may administer, dispense, or prescribe narcotic drugs for maintenance or detoxification treatment in an office-based opioid treatment program.</p>]]></text>
